      <h2>Full-Service General Contracting Across Maui</h2>
      <p>When you're looking for construction companies on Maui, the options range from large commercial firms to solo handymen with no license. Great General LLC sits in a different category: a small, focused general contracting operation where the owner — Noel — is directly involved in every project from the first site visit through final punch list.</p>

      <p>We hold a Hawaii DCCA B License (General Building Contractor), which is one of the most comprehensive contractor licenses issued in Hawaii. It allows us to self-perform the core trades — carpentry, framing, drywall installation and finishing, interior and exterior demolition, and more — without routing that work through subcontractors. For property owners on Maui, that means less overhead, more direct accountability, and a contractor who actually knows what's happening on your job site every day.</p>

      <p>We've been operating on Maui for five-plus years. In that time, we've worked on residential homes from Haiku to Kihei, vacation rental units from Wailea to Ka'anapali, and commercial tenant improvements in Kahului and Wailuku. The island presents unique construction challenges — limited material supply chains, coastal environmental conditions, Maui County's specific permitting process, and the logistical reality of working on an island — and we've navigated all of it firsthand.</p>

      <h2>What General Contracting Includes</h2>
      <p>General contracting is the discipline that ties every element of a construction project together. Here's what Great General LLC provides as your general contractor on Maui:</p>

      <h3>Scope &amp; Permit Planning</h3>
      <p>Every project starts with a clear scope of work. Before any permit application is filed or any work begins, we walk through the project with you in detail — what's included, what the construction sequence looks like, and what the realistic timeline and budget range are. There are no vague estimates that balloon later; we define the scope clearly upfront.</p>
      <p>For projects that require Maui County Department of Public Works permits — and most projects of any significant scale do — we handle the application process entirely. This includes preparing the permit documents, interfacing with county plan reviewers, scheduling inspections, and walking through the final inspection sign-off. Many property owners are unaware of which projects require permits; we'll advise you honestly from the first meeting.</p>

      <h3>Project Management</h3>
      <p>Once work begins, project management means something specific to us: Noel is on-site or in direct communication daily. There's no layers of supervision between the person you called and the people doing the work. Scheduling, material procurement, crew coordination, and quality control are all managed by the same person who gave you your estimate and signed your contract.</p>
      <p>We work on residential homes, condominiums, vacation rental units, and small commercial properties. Projects range from single-room renovations to full gut-and-rebuild remodels. Regardless of scale, the management approach is the same: clear communication, documented progress, and no surprises at invoice time.</p>

      <h3>Self-Performing Core Trades</h3>
      <p>The B License gives us a distinct advantage over general contractors who rely entirely on subcontractors. We self-perform carpentry, interior and exterior framing, drywall installation and finishing, selective demolition, full demolition, interior millwork and custom carpentry, and various finishing trades. This keeps your project on schedule (no waiting for a sub with a full calendar), reduces costs (no subcontractor markup), and keeps quality control in a single pair of hands.</p>

      <h3>Coordination of Specialty Trades</h3>
      <p>Where specialized licensed trades are required — electrical, plumbing, HVAC, roofing — we coordinate directly with licensed specialty contractors who understand Maui's market and building code requirements. We manage their scheduling, quality, and integration into the overall project timeline so you're not juggling five different contractors.</p>

      <h2>Projects We Handle</h2>
      <p>Our general contracting work spans a wide range of project types on Maui:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Residential remodels and additions</strong> — kitchen and bathroom renovations, room additions, garage conversions, ADU (accessory dwelling unit) construction, and whole-home renovations across Maui's residential communities.</li>
        <li><strong>Vacation rental renovations</strong> — full unit refreshes, ADA compliance upgrades, kitchen and bathroom remodels, flooring replacement, and layout modifications for vacation rental properties in Kihei, Wailea, Lahaina, and surrounding areas. We understand the rental calendar and work to minimize vacancy time.</li>
        <li><strong>Condominium improvements</strong> — interior renovation work within condo units on Maui, coordinated with HOA requirements and building management rules. We know the process for working within Maui's condominium communities.</li>
        <li><strong>Commercial tenant improvements</strong> — interior buildouts and remodels for commercial tenants in Kahului, Wailuku, and Kihei. From office renovations to retail buildouts, we handle the permitting and construction management for commercial spaces.</li>
        <li><strong>New construction coordination</strong> — for new residential construction projects, we manage subcontractor coordination, permit tracking, inspection scheduling, and construction sequencing to keep complex builds on track.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why Hawaii's B License Matters</h2>
      <p>Hawaii's contractor licensing system is structured around the work a contractor is legally authorized to perform. A General Building (B) License authorizes the holder to perform work that is incidental to, or supplementary to, the general construction of a building. In practice, this means we can legally perform the structural and finish work that makes up the bulk of most residential and commercial construction projects.</p>
      <p>Hiring an unlicensed contractor or a contractor performing work outside their license scope creates significant risk: unpermitted work, insurance voidance, difficulty selling or refinancing the property, and no legal recourse if the work is defective. When you hire Great General LLC, you're working with a licensed, insured contractor who operates within the law and pulls permits when required.</p>

      <h2>Maui County Permit Process</h2>
      <p>Maui County's Department of Public Works and Environmental Management handles building permits for all construction in unincorporated Maui County. The permitting process on Maui has specific requirements, review timelines, and inspection sequences that differ from what you may have encountered on the mainland.</p>
      <p>We've been through the Maui County permit process many times across a range of project types. We know which projects require over-the-counter permits, which require full plan review, and how to prepare documentation that moves efficiently through the review process. Permit handling is included in our general contracting scope — it's not an add-on or an afterthought.</p>

      <h2>Serving All Communities on Maui</h2>
      <p>We provide general contracting services across the entire island — Kihei, Wailea, Makena, Lahaina, Ka'anapali, Kapalua, Wailuku, Kahului, Paia, Haiku, Makawao, and surrounding communities. There's no extra travel charge for South Maui or Upcountry projects; Maui is our service area in full.</p>

      <h2>Get a Free On-Site Estimate</h2>
      <p>If you have a construction project on Maui — from a bathroom renovation to a full home remodel to a commercial tenant improvement — call us or submit an estimate request online. We'll schedule a free on-site visit, walk through the scope with you, and give you a clear, written estimate. No charge, no obligation, no pressure.</p>
